         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 3226, recto: (1) Pamonthes, son of Pates, son of Pakhembik, has paid (2) to the bank of the northern houses for silver of poll (3) of year 41 in Jeme, 2 staters / 1 stater (4) 2 staters again. Likewise, for the bath (tax), (5) 1 kite. Written in year 41, Pharmouthi 18. (6) Likewise, on that day, for the weavers&amp;apos; tax (7) of year 41, 1/2 kite, 5 obols / 5 1/2 obols (8) / 1/2 kite, 5 obols again.</ab>
